sentences: Ron Tarrant (born 11 October 1988) is a Canadian Producer/ Writer/ Voice-Over Artist/ Sound Designer as well as Singer/Guitarist/Producer in the band Lost in Film.
(2006–2008)', Tarrant worked for Roger's Media in Calgary, Alberta, Canada as a show producer for Calgary Flames Radio and the Fan 960 as a featured on-air announcer.
(2008–2009)', Moved to Tiessen Media in Airdrie, Alberta as their production manager and midday host from 11-2pm.
While at the Range, Tarrant presented Walt Disney Studios with their radio trailer for the 2008 film The Chronicles of Narnia: Prince Caspian providing the voice over and production.

(2009–2012)', Returned to Rogers Media in Calgary, Alberta as Imaging & Commercial Producer with 96.9 Jack FM, Lite 95.9, 660 News, Sportsnet Radio-Fan 960 & 106.5 Mountain FM.(2012–2013)' Promoted to Rogers Media's- 91.7

(2013–2016)' Promoted to Rogers Media's flagship CHR radio station -KISS 92.5 in Toronto, Ontario, Canada, as National Imaging Producer and station Sound Designer.
(2016–2019)'  Tarrant was recruited to join the Howard Stern Show/Channels in New York City with SiriusXM Satellite Radio, as Head Imaging & Sound Designer, as well as voice of Howard 100/
(2019–Current)' Director at ReelWorld Productions (USA/UK) internationally.
Tarrant was featured in Professional Sound Magazine (May 2014 & November 2019), and published several times in the Radio & Production International Magazine (RAP).

(2008–2012) Lead guitar player in Calgary based band Broken Ride, Broken Ride has received moderate success with their first single "Find That Place"-(2009) from their debut EP on rock radio stations across Canada.

(2008–2012) Lead guitar player in Calgary based band Broken Ride, Broken Ride has received moderate success with their first single "Find That Place"-(2009) from their debut EP on rock radio stations across Canada.
In March of (2011) Broken Ride released their first LP Everything Considered.
The band's single "Run" won the 2013 Regional Canadian Radio Star Award for "Best Song" at Canadian Music Week.
(2012–2013) Tarrant joined the award-winning Edmonton band "Mars & Venus" as another guitarist for the recording of their 2nd 5-song EP "New Era" in the winter of 2012.
